```java
class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }
        while (n % 3 == 0) {
            n = n / 3;
        }
        return n == 1;
    }
}
```

This function works by repeatedly dividing the number by 3 until it is either 1 or 0. If it is 1, then the number is a power of 3. If it is 0, then the number is not a power of 3.

